description:
The classic nineties British documentary explores the haunted stories and legendary ghosts behind the British Isles's castles.

From the London Tower to stately Fyvie Castle, ghosts lurk in the halls of history for the British Isles. Myths, legends, and tragedies surrounding these sites are explored in a series of episodes chronicling the history of haunted castles across the United Kingdom and Ireland.

Narrated by celebrated actor Robert Hardy, his voice lends a rich and playful commentary as the series explores the spooky legends and the modern-day state of the British Isles's most haunted estates. From lighthearted legends to tales of dark forces at work, the DVD documentary offers prime entertainment for history buffs and ghost story lovers.

